---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  pageType="guide"
  guideTopic="condition"
  title="New vs Used Shipping Containers - Condition Guide | Steel Box Direct"
  description="Understand shipping container condition grades. Compare new (one-trip), cargo-worthy, wind & water tight, and as-is containers."
  datePublished="2026-03-10"
  dateModified="2026-05-26"
>
  <div class="guide-header guide_header" style="background: var(--c2-cond); color: var(--cream);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sh guide_eyebrow" style="border-color: var(--cream);">
        <span class="idx">§ 02</span>
        <span class="nm" style="color: var(--cream);">Decision: Condition</span>
        <span class="tg" style="color: var(--cream);">ISO 9096 Standards</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="big guide_headline" style="color: var(--cream);">New or Used?<br><em>Know the Trade-off.</em></h1>
      <p class="guide-lede guide_lede" style="opacity: .9;">
        New containers guarantee weather protection for expensive equipment. Used containers cost 40–60% less
        but vary in durability. Let's break down what each grade means in practice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="guide-content guide_content">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="row guide_main_row">
        <div class="main-col guide_main_col">
          <h2>Understanding Container Grades</h2>
          <p>Shipping containers are graded by their remaining useful life. These grades are industry-standard, though exact naming varies by seller.</p>
          <p style="font-weight: 600;">Our default stock is cargo-worthy (used) — structurally sound and weather-tight, the grade most buyers need. New (one-trip) units are available on request; just ask during your quote call.</p>

          <div class="grade-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--c2-cond);">
            <h3>New / One-Trip</h3>
            <div class="m guide_comparison_item_meta" style="color: var(--c2-cond); margin-bottom: 12px;">Effective Lifetime: 20+ Years</div>
            <p>Manufactured overseas, sailed once, then sold. Effectively brand-new with zero rust and perfect seals.</p>
            <div class="who guide_comparison_item_tag">→ Tom · John Deere protection</div>
          </div>

          <div class="grade-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--yellow);">
            <h3>Cargo Worthy (CW)</h3>
            <div class="m guide_comparison_item_meta" style="color: var(--yellow-d); margin-bottom: 12px;">The Sweet Spot · 15+ Years</div>
            <p>Certified structurally sound for shipping. Looks worn (surface rust, dents) but function is equivalent to new for storage.</p>
            <div class="who guide_comparison_item_tag" style="background: var(--yellow); color: var(--ink);">→ Best Value for Farm Use</div>
          </div>

          <div class="grade-card guide_comparison_item" style="border-left-color: var(--ink);">
            <h3>Wind & Water Tight (WWT)</h3>
            <div class="m guide_comparison_item_meta" style="color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 12px;">Budget Option · 10+ Years</div>
            <p>Retired from shipping. Still keeps weather out, but expect heavy cosmetic wear and more maintenance over time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar-col guide_sidebar_col">
          <div class="authority-card guide_callout">
            <div class="m guide_callout_label">The Reality Check</div>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>87%</strong> of farm buyers choose cargo-worthy used units.</li>
              <li><strong>$ / sq ft</strong> is 50% lower on used vs new.</li>
              <li><strong>Appearance</strong> accounts for 73% of the price premium on new units.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="cta-card guide_cta">
            <h4 class="guide_cta_headline">Ready to quote?</h4>
            <p>We'll give you a real number for both grades.</p>
            <a href="/quote/" class="btn guide_cta_btn">Get My Quote <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .guide-header {
      padding: 80px 0 64px;
      border-bottom: 2.5px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .guide-lede {
      font-size: 22px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      margin: 40px 0 0;
      max-width: 720px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .guide-content {
      padding: 96px 0;
      background: var(--cream);
    }

    .row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
      gap: 80px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .grade-card {
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      border-left: 8px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--ink);
    }
    .grade-card h3 {
      font-family: var(--narrow);
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 28px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    .who {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: .08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 4px 8px;
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .authority-card {
      background: var(--ink);
      color: var(--cream);
      padding: 32px;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    }
    .authority-card .m { color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .authority-card li { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.45; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(246,241,231,.1); padding-bottom: 16px; }
    .authority-card li:last-child { border: none; }

    .cta-card {
      margin-top: 40px;
      background: white;
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--c1-size);
    }
    .cta-card h4 { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 24px; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .cta-card p { font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 20px; }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
      .guide-header { padding: 48px 0; }
      .big { font-size: clamp(48px, 10vw, 80px); }
    }
    .guide-next { padding: 48px 0; background: var(--ink); border-top: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08); }
    .guide-next-label { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .1em; color: var(--yellow); margin-bottom: 16px; }
    .guide-next-links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; }
    .guide-next-links a { font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: 17px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--cream); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); padding-bottom: 2px; }
    .guide-next-links a:hover { color: var(--yellow); border-color: var(--yellow); }
  </style>

  <section class="guide-next">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="guide-next-label">Continue researching</p>
      <div class="guide-next-links">
        <a href="/cost/">What does a container cost?</a>
        <a href="/permits/">Do I need a permit?</a>
        <a href="/delivery/">How is it delivered?</a>
        <a href="/shipping-containers-for-sale/">Browse container specs</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="guide-product-cta" style="padding: 64px 0; background: var(--ink); color: var(--cream);">
    <div class="wrap" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 24px; max-width: 680px;">
      <p class="m" style="color: var(--yellow); margin: 0;">Ready to buy?</p>
      <h2 style="font-family: var(--narrow); font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 0; line-height: 1.05;">Browse containers by condition</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 17px; opacity: .75; margin: 0; line-height: 1.5;">Cargo-worthy (used) by default, with new (one-trip) on request — see what's available in your area.</p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/shipping-containers-for-sale/" class="btn" style="background: var(--yellow); color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--yellow);">View All Containers →</a>
        <a href="/shipping-containers-for-sale/40-foot-high-cube-container/" class="btn-ghost" style="color: var(--cream);">40ft High Cube</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
